**Identifying the New Administrative Unit**

Next, I need to pinpoint the specific ward, "Xã Đông Cơ", within its old district, "Huyện Tiền Hải", even though we're eliminating districts. I know the resolutions will still reference them for context. I'm focusing on "Xã Đông Cơ".

"Đông Cơ" is right there, merged into "Đồng Châu". This is a strong match.

I'll quickly cross-check to make sure there are no other relevant mentions of "Đông Cơ" or "Tiền Hải". Looking through the other lines in the resolution, nothing else fits.

Finally, I consult the "New wards" list and confirm that "Xã Đồng Châu" does indeed fall under "Tỉnh Hưng Yên". The data I have confirms that "Xã Đồng Châu" has the code "13003".

The citation, of course, is from resolution "1666/NQ-UBTVQH15", specifically line 48. I'm very confident, a high "confidence" level, since "Đông Cơ" is explicitly a part of the new ward "Đồng Châu" in the resolution, and the province merger is clear. That's a solid finding.
